				<div class="content">
					<div id="post_message_1469403">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							For Europeans:<br />
<br />
<a href="http://www.videogamesplus.ca" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">www.videogamesplus.ca</a> (not .com)<br />
<br />
They ship videogames as &quot;toy game&quot; valued at $20, which will bypass most countries import regulations, as it is cheap. With video game systems they ship them as &quot;repaired replacement system&quot; at $20.<br />
<br />
Of course, the games need to be region free, so the PS3 gets a bit cheaper in the long run as the 360 has quite a few region coded games. My savings are around $20-30 per game compared to the retail price in Norway.<br />
<br />
Shipping is $7 Canadian per game, no matter how many you order. <br />
<br />
Ebay works as well if you get people to ship it without stating the actual cost, and ship it as a gift.<br />
<br />
Amazon is crap as it ships with the full sale price, never ordered anything from them that have managed to ship through customs even if I stated specifically how I wanted them to mark the item.
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
