				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					Re: How to save money when buying videogames
				</h2>
				

						
						
				<div class="content">
					<div id="post_message_1469509">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							Another thing is sell your used games.  I use half.com because I can just put it up there and wait for the email to tell me it has sold.  This way I don't have to worry about timing auction endings and the like.  I tend to buy my games used from here as well.<br />
<br />
If you sell them yourself, you are going to get much better rates than using Gamestop.  The only time I get something from Gamestop is when they do a buy 2 get 3rd free deal on used games.  Then their used prices are decent.<br />
<br />
Check Black Friday deals.  They usually have a relatively new release for cheap.  The last few years I got Bioshock, Orange Box, Superman Returns (yech), Marvel Ultimate Alliance for $20 new within like 3 weeks of release.  I also got Dead Space last year for $30 new from Target.  I sold these games on half.com for more than I paid for them after finishing them.
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
