				<div class="message">Please note the region encoding of whatever you buy, some systems are region free and some are not. PS3 I know, and I think PSP.</div>
			
		</div>
	</div>
</div><ul><li style=""><b>DS</b>: DS games are <font color="green">region free</font>.</li><li style=""><b>DSi</b>: DSi games are <font color="red">region coded</font>, but regular DS games will play on any DSi.</li><li style=""><b>PS3</b>: PS3 games are <font color="green">region free</font>. PS1 and PS2 games are <font color="red">region coded</font> and that restriction is enforced on the PS3. Blu-ray movies are <font color="orange">optionally region coded</font>.</li><li style=""><b>PSP</b>: PSP games are <font color="green">region free</font>. UMD movies are <font color="red">region coded</font>.</li><li style=""><b>Wii</b>: Wii games are <font color="red">region coded</font>. GameCube games are <font color="red">region coded</font>.</li><li style=""><b>Xbox 360</b>: Games are <font color="orange">optionally region coded</font>. <a href="http://www.play-asia.com/paOS-00-3-xbox360_compatibility_guide-49-en.html" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Xbox 360 Region Compatibility List</a>.</li></ul>
						</blockquote>
