				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					Re: How to save money when buying videogames
				</h2>
				

						
						
				<div class="content">
					<div id="post_message_1470706">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							<div class="bbcode_container">
	<div class="bbcode_quote">
		<div class="quote_container">
			<div class="bbcode_quote_container"></div>
			
				<div class="bbcode_postedby">
					<img src="images/misc/quote_icon.png" alt="Quote" /> Originally Posted by <strong>Droigan</strong>
					<a href="showthread.php?s=030b5bb1eeef6c38cdd5e1505647e8e4&amp;p=1470132#post1470132" rel="nofollow"><img class="inlineimg" src="images/buttons/viewpost-right.png" alt="View Post" /></a>
				</div>
				<div class="message">Since steam just switched from the US dollar to Euros without bothering converting the currency difference, Steam has become quite expensive here. So their old games sales weekends are usually no more cheap than the local store bargain bins, in some cases Steam is even more expensive than retail now which is crazy considering Norwegian retail prices.</div>
			
		</div>
	</div>
</div>Now that's a bit exaggerated. Steam just has to charge more euro's for a product so you folk can have all your fancy social services. They don't use the same price and just stick a dollars or euro sign in front of it.
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
